<!WA6><img src="http://www.ccs.neu.edu/home/shankara/verse4.gif" width=300> <P>
Children, not the wise, speak of SANKHYA (Theory) and YOGA (Practice) as distinct; he who is truly established even in one, obtains the fruits of both. <P>
<!WA7><img src="http://www.ccs.neu.edu/home/shankara/verse5.gif" width=300> <P>
That place which is reached by SANKHYAS (men of theory) is also reached by the YOGINS (men of action); for SANKHYA (theory) and YOGA (practice) are all one : he who sees [that this is true], he sees [indeed]. <P>

- Lord Krishna in the Bhagavad Gita, Chap. 5, verses 4-5.
